<topic id="_setup_any_project">
   <title>Setup any project</title>
   <body>
      <p>To enable Test Scenario in your project, follow the below steps:</p>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>
               <b>Add the required Test Scenario dependency</b>:
Add the following dependency to your projectâ€™s <tt>pom.xml</tt> to enable the Test Scenario runner:</p>
            <codeblock outputclass="language-console">
   &lt;dependency&gt;
     &lt;groupId&gt;org.kie.kogito&lt;/groupId&gt;
     &lt;artifactId&gt;kogito-scenario-simulation&lt;/artifactId&gt;
     &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
   &lt;/dependency&gt;
</codeblock>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
               <b>Create <tt>KogitoScenarioJunitActivatorTest.java</tt>
               </b>:
Create the <tt>KogitoScenarioJunitActivatorTest.java</tt> file in the <tt>src/test/testscenario</tt> directory:</p>
            <codeblock outputclass="language-console">
   package testscenario;

   @org.junit.runner.RunWith(org.kogito.scenariosimulation.runner.KogitoJunitActivator.class)
   public class KogitoScenarioJunitActivatorTest {
   }
</codeblock>
            <image href="../images/developer-tools/scesim-activator.png" placement="break">
               <alt>scesim activator</alt>
            </image>
         </li>
         <li>
            <b>Create Resources Directory</b>:
Create the <tt>src/test/resources</tt> directory for storing <tt>.scesim</tt> files.</li>
      </ol>
   </body>
